    (Black Pool Terminal) strategic direction.

    Post-correction risk level: LOW for the Rust workspace (MIT via
    Cargo.toml), UNCLEAR for src/ (Python mirror, non-runtime).

    Rationale recorded in memory/decisions.md:
    - claw-code's multi-provider routing, Ollama support, proxy support,
      and 5-layer config chain are substantially more capable than any
      legally clean alternative (e.g. ruvnet/open-claude-code / MIT).
    - Main use-case is the Rust CLI binary `claw`, which is
      unambiguously MIT-licensed.

